- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper is about generating graphs that mimic real networks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes using graph classifiers to assess generative models.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as some generative models are based on neural networks or evolutionary algorithms.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with graph structures and their properties.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as generative models are often used in AI applications.
